Zimbabwean President Emmerson Mnangagwa is meeting Bankers, Captains of industry and commerce on Monday. This as Zimbabwe is facing tough economic challenges. Since being elected into power, President Mnangagwa has been battling to address the economic crisis in that country. In recent weeks, the currency crisis, fuel and food commodity shortages have been the order of the day. Zimbabweans have called on government to intervene but not much has changed. At celebrations to mark the 19th Anniversary of the founding of the MDC, Opposition MDC Alliance leader Nelson Chamisa called on SADC and the AU to intervene. The aim of the Presidentâ€™s meeting is to find solutions to this crisis. Watch related video below: 